flowchart TD
    A[User interaction<br/>Keyboard or pointer] -->|Trigger: src/frontend/src/lib/components/QueryForm.tsx<br/>QueryForm onSubmit| B[App.handleRun<br/>src/frontend/src/App.tsx]
    B -->|Data: query string| C[streamAgentRun<br/>src/frontend/src/utils/stream.ts]
    C -->|SSE events: heartbeat/progress/sub_queries/completed| D[App.applyStreamEvent + state updates<br/>src/frontend/src/App.tsx]
    D -->|Render status/progress/answer readouts| E[StatusBanner + ProgressHistory + Final Readout<br/>src/frontend/src/lib/components/*]

    F[Keyboard focus enters textarea/button] -->|Trigger: :focus-visible rule<br/>src/frontend/src/styles.css| G[Visible neon outline + halo]
    H[OS reduced-motion preference] -->|Trigger: usePrefersReducedMotion()<br/>src/frontend/src/utils/motion.ts| I[App root renders reduced-motion class + data flag<br/>src/frontend/src/App.tsx]
    I -->|Trigger: .reduced-motion CSS rules<br/>src/frontend/src/styles.css| J[Disable decorative transitions + hover lift]
    J -->|Why: preserve essential feedback only| E
    H -->|Fallback trigger: @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)<br/>src/frontend/src/styles.css| J

    M[Frontend test guard<br/>src/frontend/src/App.test.tsx::supports_keyboard_form_submission_for_run_flow] -->|Verifies deterministic keyboard submit path| B
    K[Frontend test guard<br/>src/frontend/src/App.test.tsx::marks app reduced-motion state when system preference requests less motion] -->|Verifies reduced-motion state detection and class wiring| I
    L[Frontend test guard<br/>src/frontend/src/App.test.tsx::keeps default motion mode when reduced-motion preference is not requested] -->|Verifies default mode does not apply reduced-motion class| I

    N[Decision note: keep both JS class and CSS media fallback]
    N -->|Tradeoff: adds small hook complexity<br/>Benefit: deterministic testability + OS fallback coverage| I
